Ask HN: Is AI the Next Internet?
text:
In the 2000 the web really took of after the dotcom bust and that took us out of that crisis. Around 2008 we had mobile. This time around AI seems to be the technology that’s becoming easier to build on and cheaper for the end user.

Every week (or maybe even every day) multiple AI related posts top HN. It seems like something real is happening.

What is your take? What tech would you bet on if not AI?

Ask HN: Availability of Writable Optical Media?
text:
I'm trying to install a new OS (OpenBSD) on an Apple G5 Xserve.

This machine is unable to boot from USB, so the only options are an external Firewire drive (hard to find), netboot (possible, but quite some work to set up) or a (single-layer) DVD in the internal DVD-ROM drive.

I haven't used writable optical media in years. It seems that, at least here in Germany, inexpensive blank writable CD and DVD media are still readily available, but I wonder for how long.

So I'm thinking of a "lifetime buy" (maybe a 100-pack CDs and DVDs each), but I'm worried about the durability of unwritten optical media.

I would love to hear about your experiences with (long-term) availability and storability of optical media. Except for keeping the discs out of the sunlight and heat, are there recommendations for storing blank media?

Ask HN: What would be the best strategy to read game data from a video stream?
text:
I want to extract game data from CSGO recorded matches programmatically. More specifically, I’d like to get each player’s position on the map during the game at any given time with perfect precision (0, 1s). I’m wondering what would be the most efficient way of pursuing this. I thought of learning and applying AI-powered image classification to achieve this, but given that the UI doesn’t change much from match to match, I wonder if there wouldn’t be a more straightforward path where I write a custom algorithm to do it. Would you have some insights? Maybe there’s similar software somewhere? Thanks!

* here is an example of a video: https://youtu.be/_iofTrXtPVs
